<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000062#     1#        44.26#">Va. Code Ann. § 62.1-44.26</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_62.1-44.26"/><heading><desig>§ 62.1-44.26.</desig><title>Hearings</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig><title><emphasis typeStyle="it"> (For expiration date -- see note)</emphasis></title></heading><bodyText><p> The formal hearings held under this chapter shall be conducted pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-4009"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-4009">§ 2.2-4009<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         4009#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-4020"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-4020">2.2-4020<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         4020#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and may be conducted by the Board itself at a regular or special meeting of the Board, or by at least one member of the Board designated by the chairman to conduct such hearings on behalf of the Board at any other time and place authorized by the Board.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a_seq_2"/><heading><desig>A.</desig><title><emphasis typeStyle="it"> (For effective date -- see notes)</emphasis></title></heading><bodyText><p> The formal hearings held by the Board under this chapter shall be conducted pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-4009"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-4009">§ 2.2-4009<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         4009#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-4020"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-4020">2.2-4020<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         4020#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and may be conducted by the Board itself at a regular or special meeting of the Board, or by at least one member of the Board designated by the chairman to conduct such hearings on behalf of the Board at any other time and place authorized by the Board.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A verbatim record of the proceedings of such hearings shall be taken and filed with the Board. Depositions may be taken and read as in actions at law.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>C.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The Board shall have power to issue subpoenas and subpoenas duces tecum, and at the request of any party shall issue such subpoenas. The failure of a witness without legal excuse to appear or to testify or to produce documents shall be acted upon by the Board in the manner prescribed in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-4022"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-4022">§ 2.2-4022<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         4022#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>. Witnesses who are subpoenaed shall receive the same fees and mileage as in civil actions.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1970, c. 638; 1977, c. 291; <citation normalizedCite="1993 VA CH 897"><content><span normalizedCite="1993 Va. Ch. 897">1993, c. 897<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1993#000897#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2008 VA CH 276"><content><span normalizedCite="2008 Va. Ch. 276">2008, cc. 276<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2008#000276#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="2008 VA CH 557"><content><span normalizedCite="2008 Va. Ch. 557">557<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2008#000557#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2016 VA CH 68"><content><span normalizedCite="2016 Va. Ch. 68">2016, cc. 68<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2016#000068#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="2016 VA CH 758"><content><span normalizedCite="2016 Va. Ch. 758">758<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2016#000758#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PTM0-004G-K0W7-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hier